raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: The role of the Project Manager is to plan, execute, and finalize project according to strict deadlines and within budget. This includes acquiring resources and coordinating the efforts of team member and third-party contractor or consultant in order to deliver project according to plan. The Project Manager will also design the project’s objectives and oversee quality control throughout its life cycle.

raw_data.title: Software Specialist
raw_data.description: The Software Specialist (SS) is responsible for the software implementation support of UC application software to include Avaya Communication Manager and System/Session Manager, including integration to 3rd party applications. The SS should have expert knowledge in UC upgrade/migration processes to include dial plan changes and IP networking. The SS should have extensive experience and knowledge of programming tools used for system migration and upgrades to include ProVision. The SS works with the Project Management team to ensure timely delivery, project completion, minimizing customer downtime, and ensuring customer satisfaction.

raw_data.title: UC Engineer
raw_data.description: The Unified Communications Engineer is responsible for deploying customer projects. This can cover the technical deployment and integrity of a solution, customer satisfaction and success, and documenting project and/or complex designs.  This position will deliver customer solutions, along with corresponding documentation, and assist with development of technical design collateral.

raw_data.title: UC Technician
raw_data.description: The UC Technician provides installation, repair and maintenance support for all telecommunication systems.  This position must be able to work with customers and project managers to build and prepare systems for field deployments, work with Service Desk on Incident Management Tickets and perform system maintenance routines. The System Technician must be well versed in telecommunications systems such as IP PBX Equipment, off the shelf server platforms, Operating Systems and systems software administration.

raw_data.title: Technical Adviser
raw_data.description: The Technical Adviser is responsible for providing UC system instructions to the customer as part of the deployment project.  This can be done at the customer site or remotely via videoconference.

raw_data.title: Network Engineer
raw_data.description: The Network Engineer is responsible for designing, implementing, maintaining, and troubleshooting an organization’s network infrastructure. This includes managing LANs, WANs, VPNs, firewalls, and other networking equipment to ensure secure, efficient, and reliable data communication. The role also involves monitoring network performance, conducting regular updates, supporting users, and collaborating with IT teams to integrate new technology solutions.

raw_data.title: Network Engineer II
raw_data.description: The Network Engineer II designs, implements, and supports local and wide area networks (LAN/WAN), ensuring secure, efficient connectivity and network performance for the organization. Responsibilities include deploying and troubleshooting network infrastructure (routers, switches, wireless systems), monitoring network health, maintaining security standards, and providing technical support for medium-complexity projects. This role often involves collaborating with staff, leading small teams or mentoring junior engineers, coordinating with external vendors, and documenting network solutions and procedures. A Network Engineer II operates with moderate independence and technical authority, often requiring several years of relevant experience and advanced knowledge of networking technologies

raw_data.title: AI Developer
raw_data.description: The AI Developer is required to design and develop AI models, algorithms, and applications to solve specific problems or enhance user experiences, implement and fine-tune machine learning and deep learning algorithms using required frameworks, integrate AI models into production systems and existing business applications, ensuring scalability and compliance with data standards, and analyze large datasets and preprocessing data, with skills in feature engineering and data evaluation.

raw_data.title: Data Analyst
raw_data.description: The Data Analyst collects, processes, and analyzes data to help organizations make informed business decisions. They interpret complex data sets, identify trends, and create visual reports or dashboards to communicate insights. Using tools like SQL, Excel, and BI platforms (e.g., Tableau, Power BI), they work closely with stakeholders to understand requirements and provide actionable recommendations for strategy and process improvement.

raw_data.title: Data Scientist
raw_data.description: The Data Scientist uses statistics, programming, and machine learning to extract insights from complex datasets and build predictive models that inform business decisions. They clean and analyze data, develop and validate algorithms, and communicate findings to stakeholders through visualizations and reports.

raw_data.title: Data Engineer
raw_data.description: The Data Engineers will design, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines and infrastructure, ensuring high-quality data storage, processing, and accessibility for analytics and business needs. Designing, developing, and optimizing data pipelines for ingesting, transforming, and delivering large volumes of structured and unstructured data. Develop robust ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes to integrate data from multiple sources, validate quality, and ensure accuracy and monitor system performance, troubleshoot data issues, and optimize data infrastructure for security, scalability, and reliability.

raw_data.title: Data Architect
raw_data.description: The Data Architect designs, builds, and manages an organization's data infrastructure, including databases, data warehouses, and data lakes, to ensure data is structured, integrated, accessible, and secure for business needs. They collaborate with business and IT teams to translate requirements into robust technical solutions, enforce data governance standards, and optimize data systems for performance and compliance with regulations. This role is critical in enabling data-driven decision-making and supporting the organization’s overall data strategy.

raw_data.title: Database Administrator
raw_data.description: The Database Administrator (DBA) is responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining secure, high-performance database systems that store and organize critical organizational information. They ensure data is available, accurate, and accessible to authorized users, manage database backups, disaster recovery, and security measures, monitor system performance, and troubleshoot issues to maximize efficiency. DBAs collaborate with IT and business teams to align database operations with organizational needs, support software upgrades, enforce data governance policies, and continuously review data integrity, privacy, and compliance standards. Their role is essential for safeguarding valuable data and enabling reliable data-driven decision-making.

raw_data.title: Business Intelligence (BI) Developer
raw_data.description: The Business Intelligence (BI) Developer designs, builds, and maintains tools, dashboards, and reports that transform raw organizational data into actionable insights for decision-makers. They collaborate with stakeholders to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions, integrate and manage data warehouses, execute complex queries, and ensure data accuracy and integrity across BI systems. By visualizing data and optimizing reporting interfaces, BI Developers enable strategic, data-driven decisions and continuously support improvements to the organization’s analytics capabilities.

raw_data.title: Data Governance Specialist
raw_data.description: The Data Governance Specialist is responsible for developing, implementing, and enforcing data governance frameworks, standards, and policies that ensure the accuracy, consistency, privacy, and security of organizational data throughout its lifecycle. They define data ownership, stewardship, and classification guidelines, coordinate data quality initiatives, and collaborate across teams to promote data management best practices and regulatory compliance. This role also involves managing data sharing agreements, monitoring secure data storage and access, providing staff training on governance principles, and continuously optimizing policies to align with industry standards and evolving regulations.

raw_data.title: Customer Experience Associate
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience Associate in telemarketing engages customers by making outbound calls, providing product information, resolving inquiries, and driving sales through effective communication and relationship building. They answer customer questions, share product knowledge, process transactions, maintain accurate records, and address concerns to ensure a positive customer experience and conversion of leads.

raw_data.title: Customer Experience Specialist
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience Specialist responsibilities include providing timely and courteous support, identifying customer needs, documenting interactions, and recommending service improvements while maintaining accurate records and supporting team training. Success in this role relies on strong communication, problem-solving abilities, empathy, and adaptability in a fast-paced telemarketing environment.

raw_data.title: Customer Experience Expert
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience expert will leads efforts to deliver exceptional customer interactions through both inbound and outbound calls, focusing on understanding customer needs, providing tailored product or service information, and fostering long-term relationships. They handle complex inquiries, resolve issues efficiently, and use persuasive communication to drive sales, upsells, or cross-sells while ensuring customer satisfaction. This role involves analyzing feedback, mentoring team members on best practices, and collaborating with marketing and sales teams to enhance customer engagement strategies. Success requires advanced interpersonal skills, problem-solving expertise, and the ability to adapt tone and approach to different customer profiles in a high-paced, target-driven environment.

raw_data.title: Customer Experience Specialist-Bilingual
raw_data.description: The Bilingual Customer Experience Expert delivers exceptional customer interactions in both primary and secondary languages, managing inbound and outbound calls to engage a diverse client base. They assess customer needs, communicate product or service information clearly in both languages, and leverage relationship-building and persuasive skills to drive sales, upsells, and customer loyalty. This role requires resolving complex inquiries efficiently, adapting tone and messaging to different cultural contexts, and ensuring satisfaction across all touchpoints. Additionally, they analyze feedback, mentor team members on multilingual best practices, and collaborate with marketing and sales teams to improve engagement strategies. Success in this position demands fluency in multiple languages, cultural sensitivity, advanced interpersonal communication, problem-solving abilities, and the ability to meet targets in a fast-paced, multilingual telemarketing environment.

raw_data.title: CX Quality Assurance Manager
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience (CX) Quality Assurance Manager oversees the evaluation and improvement of customer interactions across all support channels to ensure high standards of service quality, consistency, and compliance with organizational policies. This role involves developing internal QA standards, monitoring and assessing agent performance through call, email, and chat reviews, and providing actionable feedback for improvement. The CX QA Manager analyzes key customer service metrics, initiates training and calibration programs, and collaborates with cross-functional teams to enhance the customer journey. Success in this position requires strong analytical abilities, leadership, and advanced communication skills to drive a culture of continuous quality improvement and ensure the delivery of outstanding customer experiences.

raw_data.title: CX Program Manager
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience (CX) Program Manager leads the design, implementation, and management of strategic initiatives to enhance the end-to-end customer journey and drive organizational loyalty, satisfaction, and retention. This role involves coordinating cross-functional teams to execute customer-centric programs, analyzing data and feedback to identify and address improvement opportunities, and setting measurable goals for customer experience metrics. CX Program Managers oversee post-sales lifecycle activities, from product onboarding to ongoing engagement, and report on program progress to stakeholders. They foster collaboration across departments, champion a proactive culture of customer advocacy, and ensure alignment with business objectives and industry best practices. Success in this position requires strong leadership, exceptional communication, analytical capabilities, and expertise in managing large-scale CX programs in dynamic environments

raw_data.title: CX Team Lead
raw_data.description: The Customer Experience (CX) Team Lead manages daily operations and leads a team dedicated to delivering outstanding customer service, ensuring that customer interactions meet quality standards, driving team engagement, and proactively addressing issues to improve satisfaction and loyalty. This role involves coaching and developing team members, monitoring performance metrics, resolving escalated customer concerns, and collaborating across departments to ensure seamless customer journeys and effective service delivery. The CX Team Lead is responsible for analyzing customer feedback, implementing improvement initiatives, and maintaining a high level of service consistency while fostering a customer-centric culture through strong leadership and clear communication.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert (SME) I
raw_data.description: The Subject Matter Expert (SME) I provides specialized knowledge and expertise in a particular domain to support organizational initiatives, projects, or product development. This role involves offering analysis, guidance, and recommendations, ensuring best practices and compliance are upheld throughout processes and deliverables. The SME I collaborates closely with cross-functional teams, reviews technical documents, resolves domain-specific problems, and contributes to training materials and mentorship for team members. By applying in-depth subject knowledge, the SME I helps validate solutions, improve operational quality, and drive innovation within the organization. Success in this position requires strong analytical skills, effective communication, and the ability to translate complex concepts for varied audiences while continuously staying updated on industry trends and standards.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert (SME) II
raw_data.description: The Subject Matter Expert (SME) II provides advanced domain-specific expertise and analytical support to teams, serving as a trusted resource for specialized projects or initiatives. This role involves advising on technical or procedural topics, validating key decisions and deliverables, and ensuring outputs meet organizational standards and best practices. SME IIs typically collaborate closely across departments, contribute to documentation and training materials, guide and mentor other professionals, and help solve complex issues within their area of expertise. They may also support product development, regulatory compliance, strategic planning, and process optimization, frequently acting as the main point of consultation for both project and operational decisions.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert (SME) III
raw_data.description: The Subject Matter Expert (SME) III serves as a senior authority in a specialized domain, providing strategic guidance, technical leadership, and deep expertise to influence high-impact projects, programs, and organizational decision-making. This role partners with executives, senior management, and cross-functional teams to shape strategies, design solutions, and ensure adherence to the highest industry, regulatory, and quality standards. SME IIIs lead the development of complex frameworks, policies, and best practices, oversee the review and validation of critical deliverables, and resolve highly complex or escalated technical and operational challenges. They mentor other SMEs and subject specialists, contribute to innovation and process optimization, and represent the organization in professional forums, regulatory discussions, or client engagements. Success in this role requires a mastery-level understanding of the subject area, proven leadership experience, exceptional problem-solving skills, and the ability to translate expert knowledge into actionable strategies that drive business results.
